    "Core Utilization StrategiesThis section focuses on the core components within the unified framework presented in Fig. 4, which consist of model preparation and prompt-driven generation (see Fig.",
    "At the same time, we assess three strategies: pre-training, fine-tuning, and prompt engineering, and analyze how such strategies balance the cost, flexibility, and performance trade-offs.Based on the analysis of 115 studies, we observe a pyramid-like distribution of strategies.",
    "Prompt engineering emerges as the most widely adopted paradigm (89%), favored for its low barrier to entry and high flexibility.",
    "Model fine-tuning, utilized as a means of domain adaptation, appears in one-fifth of the studies (20%).",
    "In contrast, resource-intensive pre-training from scratch accounts for a minority (4%), primarily serving the construction of foundation models."
  ]
}